menu "Button Service Example"

    config BTN_EXAMPLE_GPIO0_PIN
        int "GPIO pin number for gpio_button_0"
        default 0
        range 0 48
        help
            GPIO pin connected to the first key.
            On ESP32-S3-DevKitC this is GPIO 0 (BOOT button).
            The pin is configured as input with an internal pull-up;
            press pulls it low (active-low).

    config BTN_EXAMPLE_GPIO1_PIN
        int "GPIO pin number for gpio_button_1"
        default 2
        range 0 48
        help
            GPIO pin connected to the second key.
            Connect a momentary switch between this pin and GND.
            An internal pull-up is enabled; press pulls it low.

    config BTN_EXAMPLE_ADC_CHANNEL
        int "ADC1 channel for adc_button_group"
        default 4
        range 0 9
        help
            ADC1 channel used for the resistor-ladder ADC button group.
            On ESP32-S3, channel 4 maps to GPIO 5.
            Three voltage thresholds are hard-coded in gen_board_device_config.c:
              button[0] PLAY     ~380 mV
              button[1] VOL_UP   ~820 mV
              button[2] VOL_DOWN ~1110 mV
            Adjust the voltage_range[] array if your resistor values differ.

endmenu
